---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
import TimeLineLite from "../components/cv/TimeLineLite.astro";
import TimeLineExp from "../components/cv/TimeLineExp.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Nico Salm | Resume">
	<div>
		<div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Resume</div>
	</div>
	<div class="whitespace-pre-line">
		My skillset is highly sought-after in the computer and data driven
		industries. My proficiency in data analytics, project management, and
		process improvement, combined with technical expertise in programming
		and software development, makes me an ideal candidate for roles
		involving data-driven decision-making, software development, and
		project management. My ability to lead cross-functional teams and
		deliver results through effective communication and collaboration also
		positions me well for leadership roles in these industries.
		{/* prettier-ignore */
}
		With my diverse skillset and ability to adapt to new technologies and
		challenges, I believe I am well-equipped to thrive in the fast-paced and
		dynamic world of computer science and data engineering!
	</div>

	<br />
	<div class="mb-5">
		<div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
	</div>

	<div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10 font-normal">
		<!-- <TimeLineLite
			title="High School Diploma"
			school="High School"
			subtitle=""
		/> -->
		<TimeLineElement
			title="B.S. Computer Science, Data Science"
			school="University of Wisconsin - Madison, Expected May 2026"
			subtitle="Executive Board Member (leadership position) for the Wisconsin Quantum Computing Club."
		/>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
	</div>

	<div class="time-line-container mb-10">
		<TimeLineExp
			company="IBM Qiskit Global Summer School 2023"
			title="Participant, July 2023"
			desc="Gained in-depth knowledge and practical skills in quantum computing by completing the course and working with industry leaders, while demonstrating a commitment to professional development. "
			desc2=" Strengthened problem-solving abilities and gained insights into quantum computing applications by undertaking the intensive summer program, equipping myself with the tools to contribute to the advancement of this transformative technology."
		/>
		<br />
		<TimeLineExp
			company="UW-Madison Department of Materials Science and Engineering"
			title="Research Assistant (Materials Informatics), Jan 2023 - May 2023 (Madison, WI)"
			desc="Refactored machine learning models for materials propertiesand shared them as cloud resources through Cloud Foundry, boosting accessibility of a key resource for the materials community by 90%."
			desc2="Worked with PyTorch and Scikit-learn to run models locally before dockerizing and deploying them to Cloud Foundry, gaining valuable experience with containerization and cloud infrastructure."
		/>
		<!-- <br /> -->
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
	</div>

	<ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mx-6">
		<li>Python</li>
		<li>Java</li>
		<li>JavaScript</li>
		<li>C#</li>
		<li>HTML/CSS</li>
		<li>SQL</li>
		<li>Git</li>
		<li>Linux</li>
		<li>Unit Testing</li>
		<li>NumPy</li>
		<li>Pandas</li>
		<li>Matplotlib</li>
		<li>PyTorch</li>
		<li>Scikit-learn</li>
		<li>TensorFlow</li>
		<li>Cloud Foundry</li>
		<li>IBM Qiskit</li>


	</ul>
</BaseLayout>
